e author. Anyways I was just wondering what are your favorite books and who wrote them. Maybe even discuss the differant writing styles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ufaedaerryverwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faedaer Ryverwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raid Master</span><br>  Posts: 404<br> <font color=#778899>(2/22/02 7:47:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Favorite book?</span><hr size=1> I liked Robert Jordan's Wheel of Time. Now, it seems to be falling apart, however. The first five books tied together really well. There were references to the 2nd in the 5th, and other ties between books that made me really enjoy Jordan's style. He seems to have lost that since Rand became the Dragon, though. I'll keep reading them, however, because he's still my favorite author, and I wanna see if he reties all the broken threads. Just wish he'd speed it up a little<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br><br>Fae, among others <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uraidal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raidal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bored at Work</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#778899>(2/24/02 12:24:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Favorite book?</span><hr size=1> I love Jordan's writing style, but I have noticed he has a bad thing about not closing stories out. He does leave quite a few loose ends laying around. Although I have heard he just renewed his contract to TOR for a whopping 5 more books in the series. I do not know if Jordan can tie up all of the loose threads in these books or not, but I will read them to find out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucendarienthistletongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cendarien Thistletongue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ebonmoon.com/images/eclipse.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Co-Leader</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#778899>(2/24/02 4:52:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/chimerapop/img/cen_tmb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Favorite book?</span><hr size=1> Five more books, that is amazing. When is enough enough when it comes to books? Is his writing that amazing that it should spawn such great volume? Or is it just rehashing the same old thing? To me, it smells like the evil force called greed. I've not read this author who has made such waves in the fantasy world, though an old friend reccomended this to me years ago. I have a nasty habit of being apprehensive of all which is popular, for most things that are popular are watered down for the general public. But after hearing so many of my peers on here mention the name I'm wondering if I should investigate this further. Pardon my rambling, I get this way late at night <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Cendarien <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uzaboxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zaboxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hybrid Elder</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#778899>(2/24/02 9:27:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ebonmoon.com/images/members/zaboxx.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Favorite book?</span><hr size=1> Well, you should give The Eye of the World a shot Cen (1st book in the series). You'll see his style and can then decide if you want to know more. Very interesting series. Here comes my list of best series.<br><br>10. The Elenium by Eddings<br>9. The Book of Words by J.V. Jones<br>8. Memory, Sorrow and Thron by Tad Williams<br>7. The Belgariad &amp; The Malloreon by David Eddings<br>6. Cleric Quintet by Salvatore<br>5. Dark Elf Trilogy by Salvatore<br>4. Sword of Truth by Terry Goodkind<br>3. Elric of Melnibone series by Michael Moorcock<br>2. Wheel of Times by Robert Jordan<br>1. Dragonlance Chronicles &amp; Legends Trilogy by Weis &amp; Hickman (Origin of the DL world)<br><br>You can put most of the other Moorcock Eternal Champion series (Hawkmoon, Erekose, Corum) and most of the other Salvatore series (Crimson Shadow,Spearwielder's tale, etc.) as a good read too :P  <p>Zaboxx Painbringger<BR>Knight of the Eclipse<BR>Emissary of Arms of the Shadows of the Ebon Moon<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ufaedaerryverwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faedaer Ryverwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raid Master</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#778899>(2/25/02 5:42:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Favorite book?</span><hr size=1> David Eddings... ooh... As far as Jordan goes, I would recommend the first five of the Wheel of Time. After that, he loses it. Raidal and I will let you know if it gets all tied back together, but... through the first five. Ooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo. Makes all of the D&amp;D based books look like children wrote them. Eddings is similar, he just gets to a point. Problem -like I said- is Jordan either lost his train of thought after five books, or they will all be tied back up. He's got a contract for five more books. The next one would fall under the old contract.<br>I'm a die-hard Jordan fan. Read the first five and you'll understand. Past that I'm dissapointed. He apparently lost his train of thought. But I used to dream about his books when I fell asleep reading them. They were powerful.<br>Try 'em and see.<br>Nowdays, I don't read, I play. I'm still waiting on Rand to pull all that @#%$ together.<br>I forgot about Eddings, though. I'll go buy some books and read.<br>Thanks Zab. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uraidal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raidal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bored at Work</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#778899>(2/25/02 6:26:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Favorite book?</span><hr size=1> Hehe I have read part of the next Jordan book(supposedly. Found it on a fan site so it is not probally written by Jordan, but if it is he actually starts to tie up some really lost threads.)<br>I also forgot another series I loved. It is a series of books called Prophecy, Rhapsody, and the third title escapes me. I think Elizabeth Haydon was the author, but it has been awhile since I read them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ufaedaerryverwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faedaer Ryverwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raid Master</span><br>  Posts: 422<br> <font color=#778899>(2/26/02 6:50:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ebonmoon.com/images/members/faedaer.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Favorite book?</span><hr size=1> What about Anne McCaffrey? She's really good too. The Pern chronicles and such. Those were really good. <p>Faedaer Ryverwalker<BR>Siege Captain<BR>Keeper of the Fist <BR>Woodland Priest of Tunare<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/usonorusvocalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sonorus Vocalis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#778899>(2/27/02 7:21:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  OMG</span><hr size=1> OMG i cant belive no one has said Neal Stephenson!! i love his books so it might just be me hehehe. he writes cyberpunk stuff, he hes 3 major books out right now and i recomend them to everyone, they are: 1) Snow Crash 2) Diamond Age and 3) Cryptonomicon. also China Melville's Perdido Street Station is an awesome book, i HIGHLY recomend all 4! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucendarienthistletongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cendarien Thistletongue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ebonmoon.com/images/eclipse.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Co-Leader</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#778899>(3/1/02 4:15:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/chimerapop/img/cen_tmb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: OMG</span><hr size=1> Snow Crash was amusing. I liked Elric a lot too. You can all laugh at me but I used to like Gary Gygax's Greyhawk stories. Yes, very bad, I know. But I was an AD&amp;D geek, always hated Forgotten Realms crap though. I also liked HP Lovecraft. <br><br>Cendarien <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=18.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=18.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm15.threadControl?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=htt